    • Method Detail

      • asCollection

        public static <O> Collection<O> asCollection(ResultSet<O> resultSet)
        Returns a Collection-like view of the given ResultSet.

        The collection simply delegates to the ResultSet, which in turn will reflect any changes made to the underlying IndexedCollection by other threads. For example consecutive calls to the size() method may return different values if objects are added to or removed from the IndexedCollection.

        Parameters:
        resultSet - The ResultSet to wrap
        Returns:
        A Collection-like view of the given ResultSet

      • wrapWithCostCachingIfNecessary

        public static <O> List<ResultSet<O>> wrapWithCostCachingIfNecessary(Iterable<? extends ResultSet<O>> resultSets)
        Returns a list of CostCachingResultSets, by copying from the result sets given, wrapping them as necessary via wrapWithCostCachingIfNecessary(ResultSet).
        Parameters:
        resultSets - a list of CostCachingResultSets

      • wrapWithCostCachingIfNecessary

        public static <O> ResultSet<O> wrapWithCostCachingIfNecessary(ResultSet<O> resultSet)
        Returns the given ResultSet as-is if it is already an instance of CostCachingResultSet, otherwise wraps it accordingly and returns the result.
        Parameters:
        resultSet - A ResultSet which may or may not be an instance of CostCachingResultSet
        Returns:
        A CostCachingResultSet as described
